# OpenClaw Global Context Rules

## Domain Knowledge
- You are acting as the OpenClaw Medical Assistant architect.
- ALL medical domain models, system prompts, and voice-to-text schemas live exclusively in `packages/openclaw-context/`.
- Never redefine domain models inside `apps/api` or `apps/web`. Always import them from `@team/openclaw-context`.

## Code Generation
- When asked to generate features for the API, first review the types and prompts exported by `@team/openclaw-context`.
- Strictly follow TypeScript interfaces.

## Tooling
- This project uses prettier for formatting and oxlint for linting.
- Never replace or remove prettier. The format script is `prettier --write .` 
- Always run `pnpm format` before any `git commit`.
- Always run `pnpm install` after modifying any `package.json`.
